parameters: It sounds so fake... Could it be ventriloquism or something?

Step right up, step right up! Behold the rare spectacle of a
talking fox!$

Are you serious? Hmm, I went through the trouble of catching
it... but I can't resist a cute girl's request. Alright,
I'll let you have it♪
--Karin paid 3000 mon and took ownership of the talking fox.
Come here. From now on, I'm your owner. Give me your paw--
--Ouch! What the heck are you doing!?

Who do you think you are! Don't presume to be my owner
without my consent! And what's this 'give me your paw'
nonsense!? I am not a dog!
Grrr! The sound of my stomach... how embarrassing...!

You must be hungry. I work at a dumpling shop, so I can feed
you plenty?
What? I can eat as much as I want...!?

Yes. Oei's dumplings are delicious. You'll definitely be
satisfied... What do you say? Will you come with me?
Ugh... I suppose I have no choice... I'll follow...
--Karin took the fox home with her.

Such a hearty appetite... You must have been really hungry,
huh?

That sideshow owner barely gave me water to drink. I was so
famished I thought I might die.

Hmm, these dumplings and daifuku are indeed delicious.
Eating all this, I feel as if I've been brought back to
life♪

The collar that shopkeeper put on me is digging into my
neck. If I tried to escape carelessly, I might break my
neck... Seriously... It's infuriating to be made into a
spectacle like this.

How can you talk? Are you some kind of fox spirit or
something?

Well, something like that. I owe you one. I will definitely
repay this debt. What is your name?

My name is... a secret for now. I'll tell you the next time
we meet. I won't forget the favor you've done for me.
Farewell, Karin--
It... it's gone... What on earth was that fox...?

...Hmm, honestly, it's so shabby that I feel like no
customers will come like this... I want to spruce it up a
bit and add some flair.

--Karin brought some carpentry tools and started renovating
the hut!

Alright, it's become quite stylish! It doesn't feel like a
sideshow booth anymore. Let's change the name to a small
theater from now on!

--The sideshow booth has been renamed to [Karin's Little
Theater]!
Oh? The sideshow booth has become beautiful, hasn't it?

I wonder if they're going to do some new performance?
Exciting♪

Oh no!? Customers have already arrived!? I need to think of
a performance quickly...!
Huh... Are you not doing the sideshow anymore?

Yeah, I've decided to go back to the countryside. I'm
planning to quit this job. It would be great if someone
could take over the tent.

That's a shame... Take over, you say... How much would that
be?

Well, the building itself is old, so I'd like to sell it for
about 15,000 mon.
Buy the sideshow tent [15000 mon needed]
見世物小屋を買い取る【１５０００文必要】

Really? Thank you! From today, this sideshow tent is yours.
Feel free to use it as you like.
\c[17]――Paid 15000 Mon And Acquired The Sideshow Tent!\c[0]

...Hmm, to be honest, it's too shabby as it is. Customers
won't come... I want to spruce it up a bit and add some
flair.

--Karin brought some carpentry tools and started renovating
the tent!

Alright, it's become quite stylish now! It doesn't feel like
a sideshow tent anymore. Let's change the name to a small
theater!

--The sideshow tent has been renamed to [Karin's Little
Theater]!
Oh? The sideshow tent has been beautified?
Are they going to do some new performance? Exciting♪

Whoa!? Customers are already coming!? I need to think of a
performance...!

(Huh? Looks like I don't have enough money. I'll do it next
time.)
...I'm sorry. I don't have that much money.
